%description:
Tests IPv6 PIM-SM (RFC 4601/7761) over IPv6: the Rendezvous Point machinery
(Register/Register-Stop), the shared (*,G) tree, and the switchover to the
(S,G) shortest-path tree.

Topology (all links Ethernet point-to-point); the routers form a triangle so the
shortest path from the receiver side to the source bypasses the RP:

    Source -- DR_S ===== RP
                \\       //
                 == DR_R -- Receiver

DR_S is the source's designated router, RP is the statically configured
rendezvous point, DR_R is the receiver's designated router. All three routers run
PIM-SM over IPv6 (addressFamily "ipv6") with link-local PIM addressing (RFC 7761).
Receiver (behind DR_R) is an MLD listener of the global-scope group ff0e::8 and
joins before the Source starts.

Expected PIM-SM behavior, all over IPv6:
  - Receiver's DR_R sends a (*,G) Join toward the RP, building the shared tree.
  - When the Source sends, DR_S has no (S,G) state, so it encapsulates the data
    into PIM Register messages unicast to the RP.
  - The RP decapsulates and forwards the data down the shared tree to the
    Receiver, joins the source tree with a (S,G) Join toward the Source, and
    sends a Register-Stop back to DR_S.
  - The last-hop DR_R switches to the SPT, sending a (S,G) Join toward the Source.
  - The Receiver receives (almost) the whole stream.

This exercises, over IPv6: PIM neighbor discovery on link-local addresses, the
MLD-driven shared-tree join (ipv6MulticastGroupRegistered), Register
encapsulation to the RP, RP decapsulation/forwarding, Register-Stop, and the
(S,G) SPT join -- while correctly ignoring the link-local control groups
(ff02::*) the IPv6 stack joins on every interface.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: test.ned

import inet.networklayer.configurator.ipv6.Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
import inet.node.ipv6.MulticastRouter6;
import inet.node.ipv6.StandardHost6;
import ned.DatarateChannel;

network PimSmTest6
{
    types:
        channel ethernetline extends DatarateChannel
        {
            delay = 0.1us;
            datarate = 100Mbps;
        }
    submodules:
        DR_S: MulticastRouter6;
        RP: MulticastRouter6;
        DR_R: MulticastRouter6;
        Source: StandardHost6;
        Receiver: StandardHost6;
        configurator: Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
    connections:
        Source.ethg++ <--> ethernetline <--> DR_S.ethg++;
        DR_S.ethg++ <--> ethernetline <--> RP.ethg++;
        DR_S.ethg++ <--> ethernetline <--> DR_R.ethg++;
        RP.ethg++ <--> ethernetline <--> DR_R.ethg++;
        DR_R.ethg++ <--> ethernetline <--> Receiver.ethg++;
}

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: omnetpp.ini

[General]
network = PimSmTest6
sim-time-limit = 60s
cmdenv-express-mode = false
cmdenv-log-prefix = "%C: "
ned-path = .;../../../../src

#omnetpp 5.0 - 5.1 compatibility:
eventlog-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.elog"
output-scalar-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sca"
output-vector-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.vec"
snapshot-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sna"

# All PIM interfaces run in sparse mode.
**.pimConfig = xml("<config><interface mode=\"sparse\"/></config>")

# Statically configured RP. The RP node is reachable at this global address
# (assigned deterministically by Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator for this topology).
**.pim.pimSM.RP = "aaaa:1:65:0:8aa:ff:fe00:4"

# MLD on every node (hosts become listeners; routers learn local membership).
**.ipv6.hasMld = true

# Fast deterministic startup: skip Duplicate Address Detection.
**.neighbourDiscovery.dupAddrDetectTransmits = 0

# Source behind DR_S: send to the IPv6 group ff0e::8 with hop limit > 1.
*.Source.numApps = 1
*.Source.app[0].typename = "UdpBasicApp"
*.Source.app[0].destAddresses = "ff0e::8"
*.Source.app[0].destPort = 1000
*.Source.app[0].messageLength = 64B
*.Source.app[0].timeToLive = 10
*.Source.app[0].startTime = 20s
*.Source.app[0].sendInterval = 1s
*.Source.app[0].stopTime = 39.5s    # sends at t=20s..39s -> 20 packets

# Receiver behind DR_R: persistent MLD listener of ff0e::8, joins from the start.
*.Receiver.numApps = 1
*.Receiver.app[0].typename = "UdpSink"
*.Receiver.app[0].localPort = 1000
*.Receiver.app[0].multicastGroup = "ff0e::8"

# Ethernet queues
**.eth[*].queue.typename = "EthernetQosQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.typename = "DropTailQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.packetCapacity = 100

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%subst: /omnetpp:://
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# the source's DR encapsulates the data into PIM Register messages to the RP
%contains: stdout
encapsulating data packet into Register packet and sending to RP
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# the RP halts registering with a Register-Stop
%contains: stdout
pimSM::sendPIMRegisterStop
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# the receiver's DR builds the shared tree with a (*,G) Join toward the RP
%contains: stdout
Sending Join(S=*, G=ff0e::8)
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# the source tree (SPT) is built with a (S,G) Join naming the real source
%contains: stdout
Sending Join(S=aaaa:
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# PIM neighbors are learned on their link-local addresses (RFC 7761)
%contains: stdout
Received PIM Hello from neighbor: interface=eth1 address=fe80:
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# the receiver receives the stream (a couple of datagrams are lost during the
%# register/shared-tree/SPT bring-up transient)
%contains: stdout
Receiver.app[0]: received 19 packets
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
